  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Combine your<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong> and <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a small bowl, give everything a good mix up and set aside for later – this is your <strong>chilli oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and pat your <strong>tofu</strong> with kitchen<strong> </strong>paper until completely dry</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, crumble the <strong>tofu</strong> directly into the pan and cook for 5-6 min or until golden</p><p>Once golden, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the tofu is cooking, add your <strong>white miso paste</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your<strong> soy sauce</strong> (save the rest for later!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> to a pot with 800ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[1.1L] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>over a medium heat and cook for 3-4 min, stirring well to combine</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash, then cut the base off your <strong>pak choi</strong> and discard, then chop in half</p><p>Add your <strong>wholewheat noodles </strong>to the pot and cook for an initial 4 min or until the noodles are almost cooked</p><p>Tip: Separate the noodles with a fork so that they're all submerged in the broth</p><p>After an initial 4 min, add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>pak choi</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further or until the noodles are cooked and the pak choi is tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> and <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> to the pan with the tofu and cook for 1-2 min or until sticky – this is your <strong>stir-fried tofu</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the noodles are cooked, carefully remove the <strong>pak choi</strong> from the pot and set aside for serving</p><p>Add your<strong> tahini</strong> to the pot with the noodles and give everything a good mix up until the soup is creamy and has thickened slightly – this is your <strong>miso sesame ramen</strong></p><p>Tip: Stir the noodles to release their starch and give the soup a nice creamy texture</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2150Step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>wholewheat</strong> <strong>noodles</strong> in a bowl and pour the <strong>miso sesame ramen</strong> over the top</p><p>Top with the <strong>pak choi</strong>, <strong>stir-fried tofu</strong> and <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> – this is your <strong>tantanmen-style stir-fried tofu ramen</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>chilli oil</strong> all over (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
